{
  "stem": "7094.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Through the bakery where we used to deliver, there was a Polish boy, an ex-prisoner of war who worked in the bakery.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I introduced me to the Polish, uh, labor-force people, so I avoided Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I just thought, well, he made this remark because he had the documents in front of me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Surely he won't remember this after many times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's very unlikely that another coincidence-- But I lived with that fear all the time, that this boy would recognize me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This boy knew that Olga Demczyzszak was living.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This-- because I knew this boy, too, from school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he would denounce me without any hesitation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I had to stay put.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "With-- I didn't have any freedom of movement.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I worked in this home until the liberation, which came in 1945, February.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the only thing I knew about it-- that from time to time we had visitors, you know, from-- in uniforms, coming to check up if everything is run.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But normally, you know, the classrooms were run by teachers, normally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The class-- the children were looked after so that they could be well fed, uh, coming out of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Berlin was very bombarded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "An incidence comes back to my mind now.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- It must have been in 1944.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You remember when Rome fell, because Mussolini was caught.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and I listened to the wireless, and Italy fell.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I must have jumped of joy with a-- with a broom.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Somebody must have noticed that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was so-- not self-conscious, because I was on my own in the classroom, and she called me in for an interview.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she said, how is it that you are Ukrainian and you say you're so patriotic, and all of a sudden you're jumping of joy?",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
